---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words With V — Strategy for the 4-Point Tile" description="Master V words in Scrabble: VORTEX (16pts), VOYAGE (13pts), VIVID (12pts), VALVE (11pts). Only 2 V tiles in the bag — learn placement tips to maximize every play." keywords="scrabble words with v, v words scrabble, vortex scrabble, voyage scrabble, vivid scrabble, v tile strategy, high scoring v words">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words With V — Strategy for the 4-Point Tile","description":"Master V words in Scrabble with scoring breakdowns and strategic placement tips for the rare V tile.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-v"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many V tiles are in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"There are only 2 V tiles in a standard Scrabble game, each worth 4 points. This scarcity makes V a semi-premium tile that deserves careful placement on bonus squares."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the highest-scoring V word in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"VORTEX scores 16 points without any premium squares, combining V (4pts) with X (8pts). On a Double Word Score, that jumps to 32 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best short V words for tight board positions?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"VEX (13pts), VOW (9pts), VIA (6pts), and VAT (6pts) are excellent short V words. VEX is especially powerful at 13 points for just 3 letters thanks to the X bonus."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12"><article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span></nav>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With V — Strategy for the 4-Point Tile</h1>
    <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">V is worth 4 points with only 2 tiles in the bag. That scarcity makes it a tile you don't want stranded on your rack at game end. The key is knowing enough V words to deploy it quickly and profitably — ideally on premium squares where that 4-point base value multiplies fast.</p>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center"><div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points per V</p></div><div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">V Tiles in Bag</p></div><div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (VORTEX)</p></div><div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">V on DLS</p></div></div></div>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top V Words by Score</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 VORTEX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 points · 6 letters · V+X power combo</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 VOYAGE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · 6 letters · Common word</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ VIVID</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 points · 5 letters · Double V usage</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ VALVE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 points · 5 letters · Everyday vocab</p></div>
    </div>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">V Placement Tips</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target DLS/TLS:</span> V on a Double Letter Score gives 8 points from one tile. On Triple Letter, that's 12 — more than most full words score by themselves.</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play V early:</span> With only 2 in the bag, V becomes a liability late-game. Deploy it mid-game when board options are open and premium squares are still accessible.</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">VEX is your escape valve:</span> At 13 points for 3 letters, VEX is one of the most efficient V plays available. Use it when the board is tight or you need to dump V quickly.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VEX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VOW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VIBE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VENT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VIA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20"><p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p><p class="text-base text-gray-200">V pairs beautifully with high-value consonants. <span class="text-white font-medium">VORTEX (X=8)</span>, <span class="text-white font-medium">VODKA (K=5)</span>, and <span class="text-white font-medium">VIVID (double V)</span> all stack premium letters for explosive scores without premium squares.</p></div>
    <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose"><h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3><div class="grid gap-3"><a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-w/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With W — Another 4-Point Tile</span></a><a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-k/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With K — The 5-Point Singleton</span></a></div></aside>
    <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl"><div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap"><p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all V words instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a></div></div>
    <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
  </article></div>
</BlogLayout>
